President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Eric S. Edelman for the position of Member, Board of Directors of the United States Institute of Peace. Edelman currently serves as a principal with Avascent International and holds various other positions at prestigious institutions such as the Center for Strategic and Budgetary Assessments, the Philip Merril Center for Strategic Studies at Johns Hopkins University, and the Belfer Center for Science and International Affairs at Harvard University. He has previously served as Under Secretary of Defense for Policy at the Department of Defense, Principal Deputy Assistant to the Vice President for National Security Affairs, and Ambassador to Turkey and the Republic of Finland. Edelman has a Ph.D. in U.S Diplomatic History from Yale University and a B.A. in History and Government from Cornell University.